# Installing SSL certificate for a website on IIS7

To install SSL certificate for a website on IIS7, follow this procedure.

1. Open the ZIP file containing your certificate. Save the file named your_domain.cert to the desktop.
1. Click on Start >> Administrative Tools >> Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager.



3. In the IIS Manager, select the server node on the top left under Connections.

4. In the Features pane (the middle pane), double-click the Server Certificates.

5. From the Actions pane on the top right, select "Complete Certificate Request" This will open the Complete Certificate Request wizard.

6. Browse to your_domain.cert file that was saved earlier. You will then be required to enter a friendly name. The friendly name is not part of the certificate itself, but is used by the server administrator to easily distinguish the certificate. In this case consider the website to be websitetest.com.

7. Clicking Ok will install the certificate to the server.

8. Once the certificate is installed, you will need to assign that certificate to the appropriate website using IIS.

9. Under "Sites" select the site to be secured with SSL. It will be websitetest.com in this example.

10. In the "Site Bindings" window, click "Add..." This will open the "Add Site Binding" window.
